## Technical Standards

### HTML Standards
- Use semantic HTML5 elements
- Maintain proper heading hierarchy (h1-h6)
- Include meta tags for SEO
- Implement schema.org markup for podcast content
- Ensure proper ARIA labels and roles

### CSS Standards
- Follow BEM methodology for class naming
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Breakpoints:
  * Mobile: < 768px
  * Tablet: 768px - 1024px
  * Desktop: > 1024px
- Use CSS custom properties for theming
- Implement dark mode support

### JavaScript Standards
- ES6+ syntax
- Modular code organization
- Progressive enhancement
- Performance optimization
- Error handling and logging

### Accessibility Standards
- WCAG 2.1 AA compliance
- Keyboard navigation support
- Screen reader compatibility
- Color contrast ratios
- Focus management
- Alt text for images

### Performance Standards
- Image optimization (WebP format)
- Lazy loading for images
- Minify CSS/JS
- Critical CSS inline
- Cache control headers
- Gzip compression

### Technical Integrations
- RSS Feed: https://anchor.fm/s/815ca16c/podcast/rss
- Email: prismoftorah@gmail.com
- Netlify Forms integration
- Spotify embed iframe
- Podcast episode organization by Torah portion

### SEO Requirements
- Meta descriptions
- Open Graph tags
- Twitter Cards
- XML sitemap
- robots.txt configuration
- Canonical URLs

### Security Standards
- HTTPS enforcement
- CSP headers
- XSS protection
- Form validation
- Input sanitization

## Development Workflow
1. Create feature branch
2. Implement changes
3. Test across devices
4. Validate accessibility
5. Check performance
6. Submit PR
7. Code review
8. Deploy to staging
9. Production deployment

## File Organization
- HTML files in root
- CSS in /css directory
- JavaScript in /js directory
- Images in /images directory
- Fonts in /assets/fonts
- Configuration files in root

